headline: Assessing Marsh & McLennan After 10% Drop and Solid Three-Year Gains
summary: Thinking about what to do with Marsh & McLennan Companies stock? You are not alone. Whether you are weighing a buy, sell, or hold decision, it is only natural to want a clear picture of where things stand right now. The past year has seen some headwinds, with the share price dropping 10.4%. Even year-to-date, there has been a dip of 3.7%. However, if you zoom out, the longer-term story looks much brighter. Over three years, shares have risen 27.0%, and the five-year return is a robust...
